# VoteChain Flutter Rules

Mobile voter app at `mobile/`. Production-quality code only — no tutorial patterns.

## Approved Stack

- Flutter **Stable** (latest)
- **Material 3**

## Approved Flutter Packages

Only these packages are permitted. **No additional package may be added without explicit approval.**

| Package | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `flutter_riverpod` | State management |
| `go_router` | Navigation |
| `dio` | HTTP client |
| `freezed` | Immutable models |
| `json_annotation` | JSON serialization |
| `cached_network_image` | Image caching |
| `flutter_secure_storage` | Secure token storage |
| `image_picker` | Gallery/camera image selection |
| `camera` | Live camera capture |
| `google_fonts` | Stitch typography |
| `flutter_animate` | Subtle UI animations |

No Bloc, Provider, GetX, or other state/navigation libraries.

## Naming Convention

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|------------|---------|
| Folders | `snake_case` | `face_registration/` |
| Files | `snake_case.dart` | `election_repository.dart` |
| Widgets | PascalCase | `VoteChainButton` |
| Controllers | PascalCase + `Controller` | `ElectionController` |
| Repositories | PascalCase + `Repository` | `ElectionRepository` |
| Models | PascalCase + `Model` | `ElectionModel` |
| Enums | PascalCase | `VoteStatus` |

## Folder Structure

```
mobile/lib/
├── core/           # Constants, errors, base classes, extensions
├── shared/         # Cross-feature models and helpers
├── features/       # Feature modules (feature-first)
├── services/       # API client, secure storage, biometrics
├── routes/         # GoRouter configuration
├── theme/          # Material 3 theme from Stitch designs
└── widgets/        # Reusable UI components
```

Every feature under `features/<name>/`:

```
data/          # DTOs, data sources, repository implementations
domain/        # Entities, repository interfaces, use cases
presentation/  # Controllers (Notifiers), screens, feature widgets
```

## State Flow

```
Widget (ConsumerWidget)  →  Controller (Notifier)  →  Repository  →  Dio / Local Storage
```

- **Controllers** manage state and orchestrate use cases.
- **Repositories** handle all data fetching and caching.
- **Widgets** are presentation-only — watch providers, render UI.

## Widget Rules

- Prefer **StatelessWidget**; use **ConsumerWidget** when watching Riverpod state.
- Never put business logic inside widgets.
- Never call APIs directly from widgets — go through controllers → repositories.
- Keep widgets small and reusable; extract to `widgets/` when used twice.
- Never create massive StatefulWidgets.

## Screen Implementation Rule

Every Flutter screen **must reference the exported Google Stitch design** in `design/stitch-screens/` before implementation. Add a file-level comment: `// Stitch: <screen_name>.png`.

**Implementation priority (in order):**

1. Layout
2. Spacing
3. Typography
4. Colors
5. Icons
6. Animations
7. Business Logic

Never redesign layouts unless explicitly instructed. Use theme tokens from `theme/` — no hardcoded colors, fonts, or spacing.

## Example — Correct Pattern

```dart
// ✅ presentation/controllers/election_controller.dart
@riverpod
class ElectionController extends _$ElectionController {
  @override
  Future<List<Election>> build() => ref.read(electionRepositoryProvider).getActive();

  Future<void> refresh() async {
    state = const AsyncLoading();
    state = await AsyncValue.guard(
      () => ref.read(electionRepositoryProvider).getActive(),
    );
  }
}

// ✅ presentation/screens/election_list_screen.dart
class ElectionListScreen extends ConsumerWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final elections = ref.watch(electionControllerProvider);
    return elections.when(
      data: (list) => ElectionListView(elections: list),
      loading: () => const VoteChainLoadingIndicator(),
      error: (e, _) => VoteChainErrorView(message: e.toString()),
    );
  }
}
```

## Anti-Patterns

```dart
// ❌ API call inside widget
final response = await dio.get('/elections');

// ❌ Business logic in build()
if (user.votes.length > 0 && election.isActive) { /* ... */ }

// ❌ New state library
class MyCubit extends Cubit<MyState> { ... }
```
